# .cursorrules — StudyPlan AI

You are working on StudyPlan AI: Next.js 14 (App Router, TypeScript, src/ dir) + Tailwind,
OpenAI via Vercel AI SDK against a Vocareum proxy endpoint (server-side only), Supabase (auth + plans table with RLS), Vitest tests, Vercel deploy.

Rules:
- TypeScript strict mode. Avoid `any`.
- OpenAI calls happen ONLY in src/app/api/generate/route.ts. Never expose OPENAI_API_KEY to the client.
- Validate every request body with zod (schemas in src/lib/schemas.ts). Re-validate model JSON with PlanSchema.
- Supabase access via helpers in src/lib/supabase/. Assume RLS is on; never use a service-role key in app code.
- Styling with Tailwind utilities only.
- Keep pure logic (prompt building, date math, schemas) in src/lib/ so it stays unit-testable.
- Write/update Vitest tests in tests/ when changing logic in src/lib/.
- Never commit .env files or secrets. .env.example documents variable NAMES only.
- Before considering a task done: npm run lint && npm test && npm run build must pass.
